Latest confirmed cases of Covid-19 in SA 26 March 2022 The National Institute for Communicable Diseases (NICD), a division of the National Health Laboratory Service, continues to provide laboratory-based surveillance to inform the public health response towards COVID-19 in South Africa. Today the institute reports 1 497 new COVID-19 cases that have been identified in South Africa, which brings the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases to 3 712 263. This increase represents a 5.7% positivity rate. Due to the ongoing audit exercise by the National Department of Health (NDoH), there may be a backlog of COVID-19 mortality cases reported. Today, the NDoH reports 26 deaths and of these, 2 occurred in the past 24 – 48 hours. This brings the total fatalities to 99 965 to date. 23 727 513 tests have been conducted in both public and private sectors as per the table below. Sector Total tested New tested Private 12,898,512 54.4% 15,540 58.8% Public 10,829,001 45.6% 10,909 41.2% Total 23,727,513 100.0% 26,449 100.0% PROVINCIAL BREAKDOWN The majority of new cases today are from Gauteng Province (39%), followed by Western Cape (27%). KwaZulu-Natal accounted for 20%; Eastern Cape, Free State and North West each accounted for 3% respectively; Mpumalanga accounted for 2%; and Limpopo and Northern Cape each accounted for 1% respectively of today’s new cases. The cumulative number of cases by province are shown in the table below: Province Total cases for 25 March 2022 Adjusted numbers after harmonisation Updated total cases on 25 March 2022 Incident infections for 26 March 2022 Possible reinfections for 26 March 2022 New cases on 26 March 2022 Total cases for 26 March 2022 Percentage total Eastern Cape 344796 0 344796 40 9 49 344845 9.3 Free State 202141 0 202141 37 5 42 202183 5.4 Gauteng 1206002 2 1206004 507 83 590 1206594 32.5 KwaZulu-Natal 658735 0 658735 265 29 294 659029 17.8 Limpopo 155665 2 155667 18 4 22 155689 4.2 Mpumalanga 192996 0 192996 26 2 28 193024 5.2 North We